Sidebar gets raving reviews on a lot of outlets from personal blogs to larger tourist sites. Honestly, I just can't agree with most of them. Sidebar has a sleek veneer, but it feels like it collects the best things about several surrounding restaurants like Doc Crows and Mussel and Burger Bar and unsuccessfully emulates them. For the price that you pay for both drinks and food and its proximity to much better (and cheaper) establishments, I just don't understand the hype. It's a hole-in-the wall without being quaint or novel. It's a gastropub with mediocre, forgettable food. It's a whiskey bar with overpriced drinks. All in all, Sidebar is wholly unremarkable, and I would choose just about any other spot before I came here.

To be clear I came hear with high expectations. While I like the service and the food was good. The exceptionality of the place is my only concern would not hesitate to revisit. However it's not a destination. The bourbon barrel beers .....
Thai peanut salad was very good with well-seasoned ahi tuba. Whiskey sour was very good as well.

Great service. Came in for some Truffle fries to go, bartender asked my name, she did not understand so I gave her my nickname. She refused to call me by my nickname just because she didn’t understood my name and asked me to say it to her again so that she could get it right.  Amazing.

Great place for drinks appetizers, and a burger. Everything is themed around the world of the attorney, so we had the Philadelphia Attorney burger, which besides being the best hamburger I have ever had, was topped with braised short ribs and bourbon marinated mushrooms. If you are ever in downtown Louisville and want a great burger hike down to the sidebar. We plan to get back as soon as we can! Service was great too!

Closed main dining area in a Friday night leaving only the bar area for seating.  People were standing all over.  Bartender was not familiar with basic martini recipe.

Good original drinks with varied beer selections. Good bar-type food. On the downside, it was an incredibly loud environment with derby time party patrons. Perfect for after game drinks, food.

Went here for the first time visiting Louisville. Old English pub atmosphere! The service was personable and friendly. Food was wonderful!  The Ahi tuna was cooked to perfection, which is hard to find. Most places don't know how to cook it! …
Bartender is fantastic,  she was slammed and never broke a sweat. Was still friendly and had a smile on her face. Drinks are very good and fun.

This is my absolute favorite burger place in town.  Their fries are just about to die for, and you will want to stab your spouse if they go for your truffle fries or sweet potato fries.  As for burgers, I have never had a bad burger at Sidebar.  That being said, this trip wasn't the best they could have done.  There was nothing wrong with their BBQ, mushroom, bacon, and onion burger at all.  It was a good burger.  But, as this is one of my favorite restaurants in town, I am aware that they often make great burgers.  The only reason this is not a five star review is because Sidebar regularly blows me away, and this time it was only good.
Their fried bologna sandwich is nails and they make a mean Manhattan
Really good burger joint! Attentive staff, highly recommend.
Loved it!!!

A great place for gourmet burgers! The name is taken from the courtroom, and the names of items on the menu fit the legal theme. The food is great, and the service is quick and friendly. A tad on the pricier side, but reasonable for an occasion.
Cocktails were great
Salmon sandwich on a gluten free bun was delicious! Paired with a bourbon flight!
This is the reason that louisville has become a foodie town. One of the juiciest and delicious burgers I have had in my 42 years.
Relaxed atmosphere and good service. Always a consistent experience.

Have been here several times and every time I feel that the food gets worse.  It's a decent place to drink before a game though which is one of the only reasons I come back here from time to time.  The selection is minimal, and for a place that specializes in burgers, it's disappointing to have a poorly cooked flavorless experience when there are so few choices on the menu.
When you're  in a town you've never been to, it's the place you dream about finding for a meal. They have it going on. Do yourself a favor and eat there.
Great apps. Nice bourbon selection.
A nice place to meet and chat. A great place for an after work drink.
Great responsive service, the truffle fries are a must
First time dining here. Food and service were both excellent. Prices were reasonable, too, for the high quality of the food.
Burger was great. Service was awesome. I loved the lawyer theme.
Burgers are amazing, but dont skip out on the kale salad!
Fantastic burgers, friendly staff and amazing bourbon selection. Great place to meet before doing anything in the downtown area. I love this place.
Very good hamburgers, and very good service. Thought it was a little expensive for what you got, and thought it was very LOUD. Could not hear my wife sitting across my table.

AMAZING Parmesan and truffle oil fries! The burgers are fantastic as well. The place as super crowded when we went, but the noise was not overwhelming. Our waitress seemed distracted the entire time - even when we were asking about the menu …

Great Food and Awesome Service...True to the Midwest Hospitality...a must visit if you're in Louisville KY

Burgers and bourbon list were good! A little pricy for the quality food and bourbon prices were a bit higher than others, but it was a good experience. The staff was friendly and helpful. Loaded fries were awesome, zucchini fries not so much.
Loved the gluten free options!
Delicious creative burger combinations
Burgers and bourbon are amazing

Never had a bad meal here. Always excellent.
Great bar before or after Yum!

We were so excited to find this local gem in Louisville. Atmosphere was great, food was amazing, and Lisa, our server, was incredible! We will definitely be back here! Highly recommend the "Cardinal Mimosa," beer cheese dip with pretzels appetizer, and the burgers were out of this world. Sit in the bar and definitely ask for Lisa.
The Thai salad was wonderful and the burgers looked amazing!

Great little gem.They have a fine whiskey selection of unique one-offs from well known and unknown distillers. Only had small plates, but the food was nice. Ask the bartender s to school you on some whiskey and you will certainly not be disappointed.
Awesome place!  Great food and bourbon of course.  Ask for Diamond.  She was the most helpful waitress ever!
Love this place it's very cute with great burgers.
Good staff, nice quiet atmosphere (might be loud when it's packed, though).
The best burgers in the ville.   Grab the beer cheese.
I had the "Capital Punishment" burger and it was fantastic. The burger was thick and juicy.
Awesome food. Sides cost extra so we split an the beer cheese appetizer with our burgers and it was the best decision.
Best burger in Louisville! Fries are also excellent. Restaurant can get pretty noisy.

2018.  Alabama is playing Georgia for the national college football championship.  Regulation ends in a tie.  An epic game is unfolding...  Overtime awaits... Bartenders now announce that the SPORTS bar is closing despite being fully aware …
Good food. Overpriced. Parking is a bear.
What a cool freaking place. Great food, great booze, man were they busy!

I really like this spot! First off, the staff is super friendly and welcoming.  If you're a whisky enthusiast, they have a huge menu with more selections than I can count. They also have a decent collection of beer.  I came because I was starving and the food menu did NOT disappoint! They had SO MANY good things from fried chicken to tacos to sandwiches (and one burger).  Also they have live music on some nights.
It's tight quarters but the food and service is really great!

I can't vouch for the alcohol here since I don't drink, but they had possibly the best burger I've ever tasted in my life. It was cooked to perfection and the barbecue sauce on it was not too strong and gave the dish a perfect flavor. I'd come here every day if I could.

We were staying in a hotel downtown and this place was perfectly within walking distance. We went around 1p and mostly had the place to ourselves. This allowed us to get in and out relatively fast.  Hubby and I simply shared a  burger with a side of sweet potato fries (fries don’t come with the burger - they are extra). I loved the pimento cheese on the burger and the fries tasted great with the chipotle mayo!

Recommended by the staff at the hotel we're staying at. We were not disappointed, large selection of whiskey, beer and other alcohol. Burgers were amazing, great friendly service, food and drinks came quickly and were correct. We were checked on frequently, but not to the point of annoyance. Excellent lunch.
They make excellent mint juleps
Simple syrup was made with salt instead of sugar. When made properly, my drink was good.
Good burgers, beer and service.
Great food
This is one of my favorite spots by the arena. It can get crowded but the staff does a good job trying to wait on everyone.
Good food. The sweet potato fries are particularly good.
Didn't get food, but the service was great!
Great drinks and food.
Great whiskey selection, amazing burgers.
Fantastic drinks awesome service
Huge selection of Whiskey, ( which is a plus) Great Burgers as well as some great guilty milkshakes..waitstaff is is very professional. I definitely will be back

LOVE, love, love this place. We came to this place to enjoy a good burger. We aren't from Louisville and had drooled over the pictures online. After a long hard day at the GIE expo, we were exhausted, but I dragged the hubs out anyway (because this is what I like to do is eat good food). We at first were seated in the main restaurant area and we found that it was actually louder than the bar, so we moved ourselves to the bar (the hostesses didn't mind a bit). The waitress (I wish I could remember her name but she had gorgeous long curly blondish/light brown hair & petite ) was AMAZING, funny & charming and really helped make our experience. We started off with the suggestion of the waitress with the pimento cheese fritters. OMG these were so GOOD...I wanted to lick the pimento cheese that had squeezed out off the plate....I generally embarrass my husband enough, so I restrained myself. Sidetone, my husband eats so fast sometimes I feel like I am literally in a game show to see who can eat the fastest. Most of the time I don't care because I really just care about tasting the food. NOT WITH THESE BABIES! I WAS LITERALLY LOCKING EYES WITH HIM AND IT WAS AN ALL OUT WAR....We were both going for the win! Next, because I couldn't wait until the end to order dessert, we ordered the Carmel, Apple, Bacon, Milkshake. Apparently, at this place you can get them Guilty or Not Guilty...aka with or without whisky. GUILTY ALL THE WAY BABY! lol. I couldn't have sucked that think down fast enough. So fast I didn't notice I had gotten whip cream on my nose trying to make sure I got every drop, the waitress had to tell me....my husband laughed at me (but deep down I know he was dying of embarrassment...life moves on). For our actual meal we decided to split the The Bailiff and get it with parmesan truffle fries....yummm!!!! Man, I have really underestimating the power of that pimento cheese. It really made the burger along with the bacon! This place is a win. You have to go there. You will be doing the oompa loompa roll out when you leave because you are so full.
Food was great but way over priced
Amazing burgers!

Fast-paced pub with friendly and helpful staff. Sat at the bar and had a coupe beers while we watched craft cocktails get assembled. Started with the Seafood Cocktail. Great flavor and a fair price. My buddy was more than happy with his Alternate Juror and my Death Penalty may have been one of the best burgers I’ve ever had. The beef mix of New York Strip, brisket and short rib was incredible. My zucchini fries was fantastic as was the garlic aioli.
Best burger in Louisville. Good sides and great atmosphere. Make sure to go in early if you going at a sporting event or concert afterwards.

It was a tad expensive but so worth the price. The server didn't ask us how we liked our burgers and at first I was ummmm when I seen the pink but my cousin and I would agree that it was an awesome burger. It melted in your mouth😋. Would definitely recommend and I can't wait to go back! Oh and the service was super fast as in 10 maaaaaybe 15 minutes max for the food and we got our drinks right away.
Great food and cocktails.  Decent beer offerings, but limited taps for drafts.  Incredible burgers.

Great selection, horrific service. We sat for overt an hour and weren't offered a second drink until forcefully asking for it. To be fair, our second bartender (after shift change) was beyond phenomenal, compared to the saucy little ... that we had prior.
Get the ambulance chaser burger. Good drinks
If you're looking for bourbon, this is the place. Great selection and professionally made cocktails.

Food was great. Went with a large group, approximately 20, and the service was spot on and excellent. Had the special, which was a huge burger with two patties and bacon. Hit the spot. For the way restaurants have been going, I thought the prices were pretty reasonable for what we received.
Whiskey row
Best restaurant in Downtown Louisville hands down. Perfect bar, perfect food, perfect atmosphere and best of all, perfect staff.
Great staff. Good food. Lots of liqueur. A little pricey
